text: Milly is a former commune in the Manche department in Normandy in north- western France. On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune of Grandparigny.Arrêté préfectoral 30 September 2015 Its population was 332 in 2017. ==See also== *Communes of the Manche department == References == Category:Former communes of Manche Category:Manche communes articles needing translation from French Wikipedia
title: Milly, Manche
